			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This is a great spell to use with your pet and an initial DOT spell.  Once your pet is engaged cast a DOT, then hit it with Fear...it can't defend itself, the DOT will continue to hurt it and you can hit it with a DD spell or two.  Stay just within range and Fear and DD some more.  You and your pet should take little damage if things go well, and less if they don't.
				</font>
